{"questionId":"27061","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>When heated in air, magnesium ribbon reacts with oxygen to form magnesium oxide.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Most nitride ions are <sup>14</sup>N<sup>3–</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the number of subatomic particles in this ion.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/46937ebad25a625553e183d1f00dac18070a8887.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Protons</em>: 7&nbsp;<em><strong>AND</strong> Neutrons</em>: 7&nbsp;<em><strong>AND</strong> Electrons</em>: 10 ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"27061","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ1.1e(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the number of subatomic particles in this ion.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure","2.1 The nuclear atom","Core","Topic 2: Atomic structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}